==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dichroism
<hw>Di"chro*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
two-colored; <grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ color.]</ety>
<fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>The property of presenting different colors by
transmitted light, when viewed in two different directions, the colors
being unlike in the direction of unlike or unequal axes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dichroite</ent>⟦br⟧
